Well a very happy birthday to you sir!

Hey Hadassah, Dina, and everyone else who dislikes iOS 7 because of the animations: I hear you can tone them down in iOS 7.0.3. Give it a shot, I haven't updated yet.
yes it is true .. the update helps tremendously
You could tone them down before, it was just in the accessibility section, which is not easy to find.
but the folders don't have the blow up effect when opening now
Matias, I know about that but I hear this is better.
Cool, will check it out as soon as my internet is done being owned by mavericks updates...
Lol. Mavericks, iWork, and of course the Xcode tools.
Yeah, I don't have a very fast connection (5mbps down/1mbps up), and the fact that it just downloads stuff without asking or giving a progress bar is really annoying.

(Ahhh Apple- make a product that half your users will hate, so that you 'treat' them with an upgrade to remove the features you forced on them in the 1st place :)                        also see, Windows 8 ;))
My iPod touch has reached the end of its updates. No IOS 7 for me :(
Matias Seibert, the idea is the same but as Moshe Berman and Ben Ben Wexler said this one is better... The action is the same but the result is better thanks to apple

I updated this morning. And tonight, for the first time ever I reinstalled my iPad from scratch.
I'm hating iOS 7...
It's not like I have a choice anymore...

I finally remembered to take a video of robotics class. 

The assignment was to choreograph a dancing robot. The "musical" tones are a bit drowned out by white moxie and other students, but it's pretty cool.

Check out the moving wings on that robot!
Thanks to Steve Panitz, I had lessons in this stuff from Steve Bull about a decade ago. Good times.
I thought they were not allowing CS students to take that course anymore
Wow when I took this in the summer the dance they wanted was so much shorter
I held out against installing Office for Mac for three and a half years.
I'll have to check the license terms to see if that's allowed. Sometimes they allow 3 installs.
Pages works well for me. I just want to have this around in case I need it for specific situations.
The one that I can't live without is Excel.
M$ we cant live with em but we wont survive without them
Why don't you use Open office?

I generally use Pages when I need word processing. Lately, I've been doing some copy editing and the docx files I've been getting from my editor in chief have been incorrectly formatted. In this case, only word itself will do.

What I do then is view it in gmail/google docs, and I see the formatting so at Leary if the formatting doesn't transfer completely to open office, I can see how it was supposed to look and fix it. I don't have to do this very often so I have no need for ms office. Yet.
Use wine and windows office. Mac office sucks, and runs so slow.
at least its not like itunes for windows which is a the mac version in a wrapper
Would've been better if it was. Instead it's missing core features like certain formulas in excel. And it's bloated in optimized and runs horribly slow.
It's super funny that the day after I install this, iWork gets this huge free update.
It's not free unless u buy a new Mac.
